WORKSHOP ON PROPAGATION AND IMAGING SCIENCE
University of Adelaide , 8 - 9 December , 1997
DSTO
Sponsored by DSTO Australia
To be held in conjunction with the 11 th Conference
of the Australian Optical Society ( 10 - 12 December , 1997 )
SECOND NOTICE
CALL FOR PAPERS
Researchers active in the field of light propagation and imaging science are invited to participate in this workshop , which will be held immediately before the 11 th Biennial AOS Conference . Both oral and poster papers are invited , covering experimental activity , theory and modelling , and applications .
Contributors are also invited to consider presenting written versions of their papers for publication in a special 11 th AOS conference issue of the UK journal Optical and Quantum Electronics , which is scheduled to appear in 1998 . All manuscripts , which should be prepared in advance and presented at the workshop venue , will be reviewed by two external referees
Overview talks by prominent researchers within Australia and overseas are anticipated . Speakers include Prof Michael Roggemann ( Michigan Technological University and Wright Patterson AFB ) , Prof John Thomas ( University of South Australia ) , Dr Bob Seymour ( DSTO Electronics & Surveillance Res Lab ) , Prof Jeffrey Shapiro ( Massachussetts Institute of Technology ) , Dr Garry Newsam ( DSTO Electronics & Surveillance Res Lab ) , Prof Bobby Hunt ( University of Arizona , Optical Sciences Center ) , Dr Min Gu ( Victoria University ) . Other speakers will be progressively listed within the latest information update ( see the access link below ) .
Organising Committee : Prof Jesper Munch ( University of Adelaide ) , Dr John Hermann ( DSTO , ESRL ) , Dr Garry Newsam ( DSTO , ESRL ) , Dr Michael Brennan ( DSTO , ESRL )
Topics suitable for this workshop include but are not restricted to : multiple scattering , radiative transfer in optical media , coherence , atmospheric turbulence and scintillation , speckle , laser radar / lidar , optical hazard analysis , aberration corrections , adaptive optics , propagation aspects of remote sensing
